content:
Attachment II-B Audit Report No. 4-1711
Mr. R. L. Hirshberg, PO
Feb. 26, 1962
P/SP
Excess Properties in BES Yard
A. General
BES are responsible for taking delivery at the port of entry. Normally BES take all commodi ties to their yeard and check to ensure that no damage etc. incurred during ocean shipment. On arrival at BES yard, BES advises CUSA that the equipment is in their yard. Upon receipt of this information CUSA/2nd Division advises the recipient that the commodity is in the BES yard and instructs the recipient to take delivery.
B. Equipment presently in BES Yard
1. PO No. 60.304/GS/. PO No. 5FU-338/ICA. PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00200
Welders and Parts 14 each welders & 1 box spare parts
Shipped on S.S. Hellas, B/L No. 5. Date of arrival Keelung: Jan. 16, 1962. B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on jan. 22, 1962. To date we understand that BES have not informed CUSA/2D that the property is in their yard.
This item was procured for Taiwan Power Company recommended by CUSA/JGWhite in CUSA Memo. #C2-61-1642 dated May 17, 1961.
2. PO No. 60.309/GSA PO No. 9UP-1071/ICA PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00200
Wire Rope 51 reels
Shipped on S.S. Antincus, B/L No. LA-6.
Date of arrival Keelung: December 3, 1961.
B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on December 11, 1961. On Jan. 19, 1962, BES advised CUSA/2D this item in their yard. On Jan. 27, 1962, CUSA/2D instructed TIC to take delivery from the BES yard.
This item was procured for Taiwan Power Company recommended by CUSA/JGWhite in CUS/. Memo. #C2-61-1649 dated May 17, 1961.
3. PO No. 60.320/GSA PO No. 5FU-346/IC/ PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00334
Welders, Parts & Fan, Holder, Jack
Shipped on S.S. Tremoruah, B/L No. 4. Date of arrival Keelung: Jan. 1, 1962. B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on Jan. 8, 1962. On Jan. 22, 1962, BES advised CUSA/2D these items in their yard. On Feb. 2, 1962, CUS//2D instructed the recipients to take delivery from the BES yard.
